

                    JESUS CHIST'S FRAMEBUFFER LIBRARY



JCFB is a C graphic library using the Linux' framebuffer to provide
functions to do graphic (multimedia) programming in a TTY.

JCFB provides high-level support for framebuffer memory access,
bitmaps loading & blitting, primitive & text rendering,
keybaord & mouse support. This is enough to do many things.


Build the library using the provided Makefile.


Explore `include/jcfb/` for API documentation.
Explore `samples/` for sample programs using JCFB.
